== Vectors and Dot Product ==
{{question-answer|question=60. Find an equation of the sphere with center (1,2,0) passing through the point (3,4,5)|answer={{noprint|<math> (x-1)^2+(y-2)^2+z^2 = 33</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=61. Sketch the plane passing through the points (2,0,0), (0,3,0), and (0,0,4)|answer={{noprint|[[File:Plane-intercepts-2-3-4.svg|thumb|none]]}}}}
{{question-answer|question=62. Find the value of <math>|\mathbf u+3\mathbf v|</math> if <math>\mathbf u = \langle 1,3,0\rangle</math> and <math>\mathbf v = \langle 3,0,2\rangle</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\sqrt{145}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=63. Find all unit vectors parallel to <math>\langle 1,2,3\rangle</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\pm\frac{1}{\sqrt{14}}\langle 1,2,3\rangle</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=64. Prove one of the distributive properties for vectors in <math>\mathbb R^3</math>: <math>c(\mathbf u + \mathbf v) = c\mathbf u+c\mathbf v</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\begin{eqnarray}
  c(\mathbf u + \mathbf v) &=& c(\langle u_1, u_2, u_3\rangle + \langle v_1, v_2, v_3\rangle)\\
  &=& c\langle u_1+v_1, u_2+v_2, u_3+v_3\rangle\\
  &=& \langle c(u_1+v_1), c(u_2+v_2), c(u_3+v_3)\rangle\\
  &=& \langle cu_1+cv_1, cu_2+cv_2, cu_3+cv_3\rangle\\
  &=& \langle cu_1, cu_2, cu_3\rangle + \langle cv_1, cv_2, cv_3\rangle\\
  &=& c\mathbf u + c\mathbf v.
\end{eqnarray}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=65. Find all unit vectors orthogonal to <math>3\mathbf i+4\mathbf j</math> in <math>\mathbb R^2</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\pm\left\langle \frac{-4}5, \frac35\right\rangle</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=66. Find all unit vectors orthogonal to <math>3\mathbf i+4\mathbf j</math> in <math>\mathbb R^3</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\left\langle \frac45c, -\frac35c, \sqrt{1-c^2}\right\rangle,\ c\in[-1,1]</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=67. Find all unit vectors that make an angle of <math>\pi/3</math> with the vector <math>\langle 1,2\rangle</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{\sqrt5}{10}\left\langle 1 \pm 2\sqrt3,\ 2 \mp \sqrt3 \right\rangle</math>}}}}

