{{question-answer|question=83. <math>\mathbf u = \langle 8, 2, -3\rangle</math> and <math>\mathbf v = \langle 2,4,-4\rangle</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>6\sqrt{41}</math>}}}}


{{question-answer|question=84. Find all vectors that satisfy the equation <math>\langle 1,1,1\rangle\times\mathbf u = \langle 0,1,1\rangle</math>|answer={{noprint|None}}}}
{{question-answer|question=85. Find the volume of the parallelepiped with edges given by position vectors <math>\langle 5,0,0\rangle</math>, <math>\langle 1,4,0\rangle</math>, and <math>\langle 2,2,7\rangle</math>|answer={{noprint|<math>140</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=86. A wrench has a pivot at the origin and extends along the ''x''-axis. Find the magnitude and the direction of the torque at the pivot when the force <math>\mathbf F = \langle 1,2,3\rangle</math> is applied to the wrench ''n'' units away from the origin.|answer={{noprint|1=<math>\mathbf\tau = \langle 0,-3n,2n\rangle</math>, so the torque is directed along <math>\pm\langle 0,-3,2\rangle</math>}}}}

Prove the following identities or show them false by giving a counterexample.

{{question-answer|question=87. <math>\mathbf u\times (\mathbf u\times \mathbf v) = \mathbf 0</math>|answer={{noprint|1=False: <math>\mathbf i\times(\mathbf i\times\mathbf j) = -\mathbf j</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=88. <math>\mathbf u\cdot (\mathbf v \times \mathbf w) = \mathbf w\cdot (\mathbf u \times \mathbf v)</math>|answer={{noprint|1=Once expressed in component form, both sides evaluate to <math>u_1v_2w_3 - u_1v_3w_2 + u_2v_3w_1 - u_2v_1w_3 + u_3v_1w_2 - u_3v_2w_1
</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=89. <math>(\mathbf u - \mathbf v)\times(\mathbf u + \mathbf v) = 2(\mathbf u\times\mathbf v)</math>|answer={{noprint|1=<math>\begin{eqnarray}(\mathbf u-\mathbf v)\times(\mathbf u+\mathbf v)&=&(\mathbf u-\mathbf v)\times\mathbf u + (\mathbf u-\mathbf v)\times\mathbf v\\&=&\mathbf u\times\mathbf u - \mathbf v\times\mathbf u + \mathbf u\times\mathbf v - \mathbf v\times\mathbf v\\&=&\mathbf u\times\mathbf v-\mathbf v\times\mathbf u\\&=&\mathbf u\times\mathbf v + \mathbf u \times \mathbf v\\&=&2(\mathbf u\times\mathbf v)\end{eqnarray}</math>}}}}

