== Maximum And Minimum Problems ==

Find critical points of the function ''f''. When possible, determine whether each critical point corresponds to a local maximum, a local minimum, or a saddle point. 

{{question-answer|question=260. <math>f(x,y) = x^4 + 2y^2 - 4xy</math>|answer={{noprint|1= Local minima at (1,1) and (−1,−1), saddle at (0,0)}}}}
{{question-answer|question=261. <math>f(x,y) = \tan^{-1}(xy)</math>|answer={{noprint|1= Saddle at (0,0)}}}}
{{question-answer|question=262. <math>f(x,y) = 2xye^{-x^2-y^2}</math>|answer={{noprint|1= Saddle at (0,0), local maxima at <math>(\pm1/\sqrt2,\pm1/\sqrt2),</math> local minima at <math>(\pm1/\sqrt2,\mp1/\sqrt2)</math>}}}}

Find absolute maximum and minimum values of the function ''f'' on the set ''R''.

{{question-answer|question=263. <math>f(x,y) = x^2+y^2-2y+1,\ R=\{(x,y)\mid x^2+y^2\leq 4\}</math>|answer={{noprint|1= Maximum of 9 at (0,−2) and minimum of 0 at (0,1)}}}}
{{question-answer|question=264. <math>f(x,y) = x^2+y^2-2x-2y,</math> ''R'' is a closed triangle with vertices (0,0), (2,0), and (0,2).|answer={{noprint|1= Maximum of 0 at (2,0), (0,2), and (0,0); minimum of −2 at (1,1)}}}}


{{question-answer|question=265. Find the point on the plane ''x''−''y''+''z''=2 closest to the point (1,1,1).|answer={{noprint|1= <math>(4/3,2/3,4/3)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=266. Find the point on the surface <math>z = x^2+y^2+10</math> closest to the plane <math>x+2y-z=0.</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>(0.5, 1, 11.25)</math>}}}}

