{{question-answer|question=541. <math>\mathbf F = \langle x, 2y, z \rangle</math>, <math>S</math> is the boundary of the tetrahedron in the first octant bounded by <math>x+y+z=1</math> |answer={{noprint|1= <math>2/3</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=542. <math>\mathbf F = \langle y+z, x+z, x+y \rangle</math>, <math>S</math> is the boundary of the cube <math>\{(x,y,z)\mid |x|\leq 1, |y|\leq 1, |z|\leq 1\}</math> |answer={{noprint|1= <math>0</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=543. <math>\mathbf F = \langle x, y, z \rangle</math>, <math>S</math> is the surface of the region bounded by the paraboloid <math>z=4-x^2-y^2</math> and the ''xy''-plane.|answer={{noprint|1= <math>24\pi</math>}}}}
